items.name: Adversarial-Defense-Mechanisms
items.description: A comprehensive Python framework for implementing and evaluating adversarial defense mechanisms against machine learning attacks. This project provides modern implementations of various adversarial attacks and defense strategies with interactive visualization and experiment tracking.

items.name: Machine-Learning-Based-Risk-Scoring
items.description: Our project is on "Machine Learning Based Risk Scoring" for the course Cyber Security Mangament. The baselines paper we are using is "Redefining GRC in the Digital Age: Integrating AI-Driven Risk Management Frameworks. Group 18 Members: Muhammad Alishan Mirza and Jevaan Dhamala

items.name: MultiWalk
items.description: Decentralized machine learning framework

items.name: Semantic-Framework-for-Advanced-Cyber-Threat-Analysis-and-Sharing
items.description: AI Driven Semantic Framework for Advanced Cyber Threat Analysis and Sharing using comprehensive machine learning and deep learning framework for real-time cyber threat detection, analysis, and intelligence sharing.

items.name: secs
items.description: SECS is a machine learning framework designed for structure elucidation from spectra such as NMR and IR.
